&lt;p>This code can look strange, and this is due to preserve the &lt;a href="http://docs.jquery.com/Using_jQuery_with_Other_Libraries">no conflict mode&lt;/a>. Since we like to use the $ you can simply create a function that accepts a single argument called $, then inside that function you can use $ as usual, and finally you immediately invoke the function passing jQuery as argument.  This technique is described in &lt;em>&lt;a href="http://www.manning.com/bibeault/">JQuery in action&lt;/a>&lt;/em>, one of the best book I&amp;rsquo;ve read.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>